description:
Head of State Idriss Déby "set up a health crisis management committee (CGCS) in Chad on Friday. Its mission is to:
- define and implement the national management strategy for the Covid-19 pandemic;
- Guide, coordinate, monitor, evaluate and adapt all the interventions of the actors involved in the management of the health crisis;
- In general, take all appropriate measures to fight the Covid-19 pandemic, as well as its consequences and ensure its monitoring throughout the territory;
- Ensure the effective implementation and monitoring of social support and economic support measures." 

Committee is supposed to take affect on the week proceeding May 15th. Will be under the supervision of the president and the Cabinet Ministers.
